## B) Add to Cart

---

### TC-C-01 | Add an in-stock product to cart (Positive)

**Preconditions:** User has navigated to a product page for an in-stock item.

**Steps:**
- Select a product variant if required (e.g., size, colour)
- Click the **Add to Cart** button

**Expected Result:**
- The cart item count increments by 1 (visible in the nav icon)
- A success notification or slide-out cart drawer confirms the item was added
- The product name and price in the cart match the selected product

---

### TC-C-02 | Attempt to add an out-of-stock product (Negative)

**Preconditions:** User has navigated to a product page where the item/variant is out of stock.

**Steps:**
- Navigate to a product with an out-of-stock variant
- Select the unavailable variant

**Expected Result:**
- The **Add to Cart** button is disabled or replaced with a "Sold Out" label
- Clicking (if still clickable) does not add anything to cart
- Cart count remains unchanged

---

### TC-C-03 | Add the same product multiple times and verify quantity (Edge Case)

**Preconditions:** User is on a product page with an in-stock item.

**Steps:**
- Click **Add to Cart** once — note cart count
- Navigate back to the same product page
- Click **Add to Cart** again

**Expected Result:**
- Cart count increments to 2 (or the quantity for that line item shows 2)
- The cart does not create duplicate line entries — instead the quantity is updated
- Total price in cart reflects quantity × unit price correctly
